{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}

{% set page_title = 'Guide' %}
{% set page_header = true %}

{% block body %}

<div class="flex justify-between items-center mb-6">
    <div>
        <h1 class="font-heading font-bold text-foreground text-3xl">Guide</h1>
        <p class="mt-1 text-muted-foreground">Using the numbering system</p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="gap-8 grid grid-cols-1 xl:grid-cols-2">

    {# ── Intro ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #}
    <twig:Card>
        <twig:Card:Header>
            <twig:Card:Title>Intro</twig:Card:Title>
            <!-- <twig:Card:Description>Subtitle</twig:Card:Description> -->
        </twig:Card:Header>
        <twig:Card:Content class="space-y-4 text-sm">
            <p>Value Ledger is the central register for document identification across the Value Group. It provides a
                structured and consistent naming system that ensures every document can be uniquely identified,
                traced,
                and managed throughout its lifecycle. Before creating a new document, users should verify that the
                intended identifier is available. Usage of the naming system should follow the conventions described
                in this guide.</p>

            <p>A document identifier follows the structure:</p><code
                class="block bg-muted px-3 py-2 rounded font-mono font-bold text-neutral-700 dark:text-gray-300">VG0-AAB-REP-000-000-0A Title</code>

            <p>Where each section conveys specific information, such as the responsible subsidiary, category, project or
                product reference, document type, discipline, unique document number, and revision status.
                By adhering to this convention, all stakeholders can quickly identify, locate, and understand documents
                regardless of their origin or intended audience.</p>

            <p>This guide explains the structure, rules, conventions, and best practices required to maintain a clean
                and reliable document register using Value Ledger.</p>
        </twig:Card:Content>
    </twig:Card>

    {# ── Anatomy ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #}
    <twig:Card>
        <twig:Card:Header>
            <twig:Card:Title>Anatomy</twig:Card:Title>
            <twig:Card:Description>How the ID is structured</twig:Card:Description>
        </twig:Card:Header>
        <twig:Card:Content class="space-y-6 text-sm">

            <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-x-1 gap-y-2">
                <span class="bg-neutral-200 px-3 py-1.5 rounded font-mono font-bold text-neutral-700 text-sm">VG</span>
                <span class="bg-red-100 px-3 py-1.5 rounded font-mono font-bold text-red-700 text-sm">0</span>
                <span class="px-0.5 font-bold text-muted-foreground">-</span>
                <span class="bg-orange-100 px-3 py-1.5 rounded font-mono font-bold text-orange-700 text-sm">AAB</span>
                <span class="px-0.5 font-bold text-muted-foreground">-</span>
                <span class="bg-blue-100 px-3 py-1.5 rounded font-mono font-bold text-blue-700 text-sm">REP</span>
                <span class="px-0.5 font-bold text-muted-foreground">-</span>
                <span class="bg-emerald-100 px-3 py-1.5 rounded font-mono font-bold text-emerald-700 text-sm">000</span>
                <span class="px-0.5 font-bold text-muted-foreground">-</span>
                <span class="bg-violet-100 px-3 py-1.5 rounded font-mono font-bold text-violet-700 text-sm">000</span>
                <span class="px-0.5 font-bold text-muted-foreground">-</span>
                <span class="bg-pink-100 px-3 py-1.5 rounded font-mono font-bold text-pink-700 text-sm">0A</span>
                <span class="px-0.5 font-bold text-muted-foreground"> </span>
                <span class="bg-gray-100 px-3 py-1.5 rounded font-mono font-bold text-gray-800 text-sm">Title</span>
            </div>

            <twig:Separator />

            <dl class="space-y-3">
                <div class="flex items-baseline gap-3">
                    <dt
                        class="bg-neutral-200 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded w-10 font-mono font-bold text-neutral-700 text-xs text-center shrink-0">
                        VG</dt>
                    <dd><strong>Subsidiary</strong> - Two-letter code identifying the responsible entity within the
                        Value Group.</dd>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-baseline gap-3">
                    <dt
                        class="bg-red-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded w-10 font-mono font-bold text-red-700 text-xs text-center shrink-0">
                        0</dt>
                    <dd><strong>Main category</strong> - Single digit indicating the project type.</dd>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-baseline gap-3">
                    <dt
                        class="bg-orange-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded w-10 font-mono font-bold text-orange-700 text-xs text-center shrink-0">
                        AAB</dt>
                    <dd><strong>Reference code</strong> - Alphabetic for studies; numeric for signed
                        projects; fixed abbreviations for product lines.</dd>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-baseline gap-3">
                    <dt
                        class="bg-blue-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded w-10 font-mono font-bold text-blue-700 text-xs text-center shrink-0">
                        REP</dt>
                    <dd><strong>Document type</strong> - Short three-letter abbreviation for the type of document.</dd>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-baseline gap-3">
                    <dt
                        class="bg-emerald-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded w-10 font-mono font-bold text-emerald-700 text-xs text-center shrink-0">
                        000</dt>
                    <dd><strong>Sub category</strong> - Three-digit code identifying the technical or functional
                        discipline.</dd>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-baseline gap-3">
                    <dt
                        class="bg-violet-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded w-10 font-mono font-bold text-violet-700 text-xs text-center shrink-0">
                        000</dt>
                    <dd><strong>Document number</strong> - Three-digit number unique within the combination of the other
                        components.</dd>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-baseline gap-3">
                    <dt
                        class="bg-pink-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded w-10 font-mono font-bold text-pink-700 text-xs text-center shrink-0">
                        0A</dt>
                    <dd><strong>Revision</strong> - Interim drafts use an alphanumeric suffix; released
                        versions use a numeric suffix.</dd>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-baseline gap-3">
                    <dt
                        class="bg-gray-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded w-10 font-mono font-bold text-gray-800 text-xs text-center shrink-0">
                        Abc</dt>
                    <dd><strong>Title</strong> - Textual description of the document.</dd>
                </div>
            </dl>

        </twig:Card:Content>
    </twig:Card>

    {# ── Conventions ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #}
    <twig:Card class="xl:col-span-2">
        <twig:Card:Header>
            <twig:Card:Title>Conventions</twig:Card:Title>
            <twig:Card:Description>Rules and constraints for each component of the document identifier
            </twig:Card:Description>
        </twig:Card:Header>
        <twig:Card:Content class="space-y-5 text-sm">

            <div class="space-y-2">
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-foreground">Document code</h3>
                <p>The document code has a fixed total length of 22 characters, including hyphens, and is always fully written in capital letters.</p>
                <div
                    class="flex gap-2 bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-950 px-3 py-2 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-200">
                    <twig:ux:icon name="material-symbols:warning-outline" class="mt-0.5 size-4 shrink-0" />
                    <div class="space-y-1.5">
                        <p>The separator between code components must be the <strong>hyphen-minus</strong>. Do not use
                            other dashes. These
                            characters look similar but are <strong>not</strong> interchangeable:</p>
                        <div class="space-y-0.5 font-mono text-xs">
                            <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                                <span class="w-3 font-sans font-bold text-emerald-600">✓</span>
                                <code class="bg-amber-100 dark:bg-amber-900 px-1 rounded">-</code>
                                <span class="font-sans text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-300">hyphen-minus (U+002D)</span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                                <span class="w-3 font-sans font-bold text-red-500">✗</span>
                                <code class="bg-amber-100 dark:bg-amber-900 px-1 rounded">–</code>
                                <span class="font-sans text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-300">en dash (U+2013)</span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                                <span class="w-3 font-sans font-bold text-red-500">✗</span>
                                <code class="bg-amber-100 dark:bg-amber-900 px-1 rounded">—</code>
                                <span class="font-sans text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-300">em dash (U+2014)</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <twig:Separator />

            <div class="space-y-2">
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-foreground">Reference codes</h3>
                <p>Reference codes are unique globally across the whole Value Group and must not be reused across
                    different projects or document types. They are always three characters long. The allowed format is determined by the main category.</p>
                <ul class="space-y-1.5 pl-1">
                    <li class="flex gap-2">
                        <span class="text-muted-foreground shrink-0">→</span>
                        <span><strong>Signed projects</strong>: numerical, equal to the serial number in three-digit
                            format. Can only be assigned by the COO.</span>
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex gap-2">
                        <span class="text-muted-foreground shrink-0">→</span>
                        <span><strong>Studies</strong>: three-letter sequential alphabetic code (AAA-ZZZ). Any user
                            may assign one; check
                            <a href="" class="text-primary dark:text-cyan-500 underline underline-offset-2">SharePoint
                                (TBD)</a> first for
                            the next available code.</span>
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex gap-2">
                        <span class="text-muted-foreground shrink-0">→</span>
                        <span><strong>Product lines</strong>: fixed abbreviation maintained by the Product Owners.
                            Publishing related documents requires consultation with a Product Owner.</span>
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <div
                    class="flex gap-2 bg-emerald-50 dark:bg-emerald-950 px-3 py-2 border border-emerald-200 dark:border-emerald-800 rounded text-emerald-800 dark:text-emerald-200">
                    <span class="font-bold text-emerald-600 shrink-0">✓</span>The Ledger incorporates the correct
                    reference code format per main category.
                </div>

            </div>

            <twig:Separator />

            <div class="space-y-2">
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-foreground">Revision</h3>
                <ul class="space-y-2.5 pl-1">
                    <li class="flex gap-2">
                        <span class="text-muted-foreground shrink-0">→</span>
                        <span><strong>Interim</strong>: alphanumeric suffix starting at <code
                                class="bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded font-mono font-bold text-neutral-700 dark:text-gray-300 text-xs">0A</code>,
                            incrementing the letter for each subsequent draft.</span>
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex gap-2">
                        <span class="text-muted-foreground shrink-0">→</span>
                        <span><strong>Released</strong>: numeric suffix starting at <code
                                class="bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded font-mono font-bold text-neutral-700 dark:text-gray-300 text-xs">00</code>,
                            incrementing for each subsequent formal reissue.</span>
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-1.5 text-xs">
                    <span class="mr-1 text-muted-foreground">Example sequence:</span>
                    <code
                        class="bg-muted px-2 py-1 rounded font-mono font-bold text-neutral-700 dark:text-gray-300">0A</code>
                    <span class="font-bold text-muted-foreground">→</span>
                    <code
                        class="bg-muted px-2 py-1 rounded font-mono font-bold text-neutral-700 dark:text-gray-300">0B</code>
                    <span class="font-bold text-muted-foreground">→</span>
                    <code
                        class="bg-muted px-2 py-1 rounded font-mono font-bold text-neutral-700 dark:text-gray-300">0C</code>
                    <span class="font-bold text-muted-foreground">→</span>
                    <code
                        class="bg-emerald-100 dark:bg-emerald-900 px-2 py-1 rounded font-mono font-bold text-emerald-700 dark:text-emerald-300">00</code>
                    <span class="font-bold text-muted-foreground">→</span>
                    <code
                        class="bg-muted px-2 py-1 rounded font-mono font-bold text-neutral-700 dark:text-gray-300">1A</code>
                    <span class="font-bold text-muted-foreground">→</span>
                    <code
                        class="bg-emerald-100 dark:bg-emerald-900 px-2 py-1 rounded font-mono font-bold text-emerald-700 dark:text-emerald-300">01</code>
                </div>

                <div
                    class="flex gap-2 bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-950 px-3 py-2 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-200">
                    <twig:ux:icon name="material-symbols:warning-outline" class="mt-0.5 size-4 shrink-0" />
                    <p>Don't use a released format (00) for a document still under internal review.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <twig:Separator />

            <div class="space-y-2">
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-foreground">Titles</h3>
                <ul class="space-y-2.5 pl-1">
                    <li class="flex gap-2">
                        <span class="text-muted-foreground shrink-0">→</span>
                        <span><strong>Character set</strong>: only alphanumeric characters (A-Z, a-z, 0-9) and spaces
                            are allowed, with a maximum length of <strong>48 characters</strong> including
                            spaces.</span>
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex flex-col gap-1.5">
                        <div class="flex gap-2">
                            <span class="text-muted-foreground shrink-0">→</span>
                            <span><strong>Separator</strong>: the 22-character document code is <strong>always</strong>
                                followed by a single space and then the title. Do <strong>not</strong> separate the
                                code from the title using a hyphen or any other character.</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-1.5 pl-5 text-xs">
                            <code
                                class="bg-muted px-2 py-1 rounded font-mono font-bold text-neutral-700 dark:text-gray-300">VG0-AAB-REP-000-000-0A</code>
                            <span
                                class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 bg-emerald-100 dark:bg-emerald-900 px-1.5 py-1 border border-emerald-200 dark:border-emerald-800 rounded font-sans text-emerald-700 dark:text-emerald-300">
                                <twig:ux:icon name="material-symbols:space-bar" class="size-3.5" />
                                space
                            </span>
                            <code
                                class="bg-muted px-2 py-1 rounded font-mono font-bold text-neutral-700 dark:text-gray-300">Title</code>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex gap-2">
                        <span class="text-muted-foreground shrink-0">→</span>
                        <span><strong>Casing</strong>: the title utilises <code
                                class="bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded font-mono font-bold text-neutral-700 dark:text-gray-300 text-xs">Title Case</code>.
                            Each word should start with a capital letter, except for certain short words (like "and",
                            "or", "the") unless they are the first or last word of the title. Abbreviations can be fully capitalised, e.g. <code
                                class="bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded font-mono font-bold text-neutral-700 dark:text-gray-300 text-xs">pid → PID</code>.</span>
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <div
                    class="flex gap-2 bg-emerald-50 dark:bg-emerald-950 px-3 py-2 border border-emerald-200 dark:border-emerald-800 rounded text-emerald-800 dark:text-emerald-200">
                    <span class="font-bold text-emerald-600 shrink-0">✓</span>The Ledger has built-in sanitisation and
                    character limit.
                </div>
            </div>

        </twig:Card:Content>
    </twig:Card>

    {# ── Examples ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #}
    <twig:Card class="xl:col-span-2">
        <twig:Card:Header>
            <twig:Card:Title>Examples</twig:Card:Title>
            <twig:Card:Description>Correct and incorrect identifiers</twig:Card:Description>
        </twig:Card:Header>
        <twig:Card:Content class="space-y-5 text-sm">

            <div class="space-y-2">
                <p class="font-semibold text-emerald-700">Correct</p>
                <ul class="space-y-2">
                    <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
                        <span class="font-bold text-emerald-600 shrink-0">✓</span>
                        <code class="bg-emerald-100 dark:bg-emerald-900 px-2 py-1 rounded font-mono font-bold text-emerald-700 dark:text-emerald-300 text-xs">VG0-AAB-REP-000-000-0A Site Survey</code>
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
                        <span class="font-bold text-emerald-600 shrink-0">✓</span>
                        <code class="bg-emerald-100 dark:bg-emerald-900 px-2 py-1 rounded font-mono font-bold text-emerald-700 dark:text-emerald-300 text-xs">VC1-045-DWG-020-003-01 Piping Layout</code>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <twig:Separator />

            <div class="space-y-2">
                <p class="font-semibold text-destructive">Incorrect</p>
                <ul class="space-y-2">
                    <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
                        <span class="font-bold text-destructive shrink-0">✗</span>
                        <code class="bg-red-100 dark:bg-red-900 px-2 py-1 rounded font-mono font-bold text-red-700 dark:text-red-300 text-xs">VG0–AAB–REP–000–000–0A Site Survey</code>
                        <span class="text-muted-foreground">en dash used instead of hyphen-minus</span>
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
                        <span class="font-bold text-destructive shrink-0">✗</span>
                        <code class="bg-red-100 dark:bg-red-900 px-2 py-1 rounded font-mono font-bold text-red-700 dark:text-red-300 text-xs">VG0-AAB-REP-000-000-0A-Site Survey</code>
                        <span class="text-muted-foreground">hyphen used between code and title instead of a space</span>
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
                        <span class="font-bold text-destructive shrink-0">✗</span>
                        <code class="bg-red-100 dark:bg-red-900 px-2 py-1 rounded font-mono font-bold text-red-700 dark:text-red-300 text-xs">vg0-aab-rep-000-000-0a Site Survey</code>
                        <span class="text-muted-foreground">code must be fully capitalised</span>
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
                        <span class="font-bold text-destructive shrink-0">✗</span>
                        <code class="bg-red-100 dark:bg-red-900 px-2 py-1 rounded font-mono font-bold text-red-700 dark:text-red-300 text-xs">VG0-AB-REP-000-000-0A Site Survey</code>
                        <span class="text-muted-foreground">reference code for a study must be three letters</span>
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
                        <span class="font-bold text-destructive shrink-0">✗</span>
                        <code class="bg-red-100 dark:bg-red-900 px-2 py-1 rounded font-mono font-bold text-red-700 dark:text-red-300 text-xs">VG0-AAB-REP-000-000-0A P&ID System</code>
                        <span class="text-muted-foreground">title contains characters other than letters, digits and spaces</span>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>

        </twig:Card:Content>
    </twig:Card>


    {# ── Do's and Don'ts ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #}
    <twig:Card>
        <twig:Card:Header>
            <twig:Card:Title>Do's and Don'ts</twig:Card:Title>
            <twig:Card:Description>Short recap</twig:Card:Description>
        </twig:Card:Header>
        <twig:Card:Content class="text-sm">
            <div class="gap-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2">

                <div class="space-y-2.5">
                    <p class="font-semibold text-emerald-700">Do</p>
                    <ul class="space-y-2.5">
                        <li class="flex gap-2">
                            <span class="font-bold text-emerald-600 shrink-0">✓</span>
                            Check the ledger for an available number before creating a new document.
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex gap-2">
                            <span class="font-bold text-emerald-600 shrink-0">✓</span>
                            Start with an interim revision (0A) and promote to a final release (00) only when the
                            document is formally approved and issued.
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex gap-2">
                            <span class="font-bold text-emerald-600 shrink-0">✓</span>
                            Write a concise but descriptive title. It aids discoverability and understanding.
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex gap-2">
                            <span class="font-bold text-emerald-600 shrink-0">✓</span>
                            Use the correct main category and reference code format for the project type.
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex gap-2">
                            <span class="font-bold text-emerald-600 shrink-0">✓</span>
                            Register every document identifier, internal and external, in the ledger before distributing
                            it.
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex gap-2">
                            <span class="font-bold text-emerald-600 shrink-0">✓</span>
                            Add keywords or tags ledger entries to improve searchability.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="space-y-2.5">
                    <p class="font-semibold text-destructive">Don't</p>
                    <ul class="space-y-2.5">
                        <li class="flex gap-2">
                            <span class="font-bold text-destructive shrink-0">✗</span>
                            Don't reuse an existing identifier for a different document.
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex gap-2">
                            <span class="font-bold text-destructive shrink-0">✗</span>
                            Don't skip revision steps. Every issued version must be recorded, even if superseded
                            quickly.
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex gap-2">
                            <span class="font-bold text-destructive shrink-0">✗</span>
                            Don't mix alphabetic and numeric reference codes within the same main category.
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex gap-2">
                            <span class="font-bold text-destructive shrink-0">✗</span>
                            Don't create document identifiers outside of Value Ledger. Even for one-offs.
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex gap-2">
                            <span class="font-bold text-destructive shrink-0">✗</span>
                            Don't use a hyphen between the document ID and the title.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

            </div>
        </twig:Card:Content>
    </twig:Card>

    {# ── Ledger ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #}
    <twig:Card>
        <twig:Card:Header>
            <twig:Card:Title>Using the Ledger</twig:Card:Title>
            <!-- <twig:Card:Description>Subtitle</twig:Card:Description> -->
        </twig:Card:Header>
        <twig:Card:Content class="space-y-6 text-sm">
            <div class="space-y-4">
                <div>
                    <h3 class="mb-2 font-semibold text-foreground">How to Add Entries</h3>
                    <p class="">Click the <strong>"New Entry"</strong> button to create a new document identifier. Fill
                        in each required field: subsidiary code, main category, reference code, document type, sub
                        category, and title. Also fill in search keywords to improve searchability for other
                        users. The system will automatically format and store the document ID. Once saved, the entry
                        appears in
                        the ledger and can be viewed by all.</p>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h3 class="mb-2 font-semibold text-foreground">How to Edit Entries</h3>
                    <p class="">Locate the entry in the ledger and click the
                        <twig:ux:icon name="material-symbols:edit-outline" class="inline" /> (edit) button. You can
                        update the title and other metadata. Always review changes before saving to ensure compliance
                        with the naming conventions.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h3 class="mb-2 font-semibold text-foreground">How to Search</h3>
                    <p class="">Use the search bar at the top of the ledger page to filter entries by document ID
                        components, title, or keywords. Search is case-insensitive and supports partial matches. You can
                        also use filters.</p>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h3 class="mb-2 font-semibold text-foreground">User vs Admin Rights</h3>
                    <p class=""><strong>Users</strong> can only view entries. <strong>Admins</strong> can create, edit,
                        and delete entries.</p>
                </div>

                <div>
